IMPORTANT NEWS!


bush to obama=controlled by sociopath globalists making 2000-2008 a rigged election for open border migrant crisis




Originally published in March 2007


General Wesley Clark:
Because I had been through the Pentagon right after 9/11. About ten days after 9/11, I went through the Pentagon and I saw Secretary Rumsfeld and Deputy Secretary Wolfowitz. I went downstairs just to say hello to some of the people on the Joint Staff who used to work for me, and one of the generals called me in. He said, "Sir, you've got to come in and talk to me a second." I said, "Well, you're too busy." He said, "No, no." He says, "We've made the decision we're going to war with Iraq." This was on or about the 20th of September. I said, "We're going to war with Iraq? Why?" He said, "I don't know." He said, "I guess they don't know what else to do." So I said, "Well, did they find some information connecting Saddam to al-Qaeda?" He said, "No, no." He says, "There's nothing new that way. They just made the decision to go to war with Iraq." He said, "I guess it's like we don't know what to do about terrorists, but we've got a good military and we can take down governments." And he said, "I guess if the only tool you have is a hammer, every problem has to look like a nail."

So I came back to see him a few weeks later, and by that time we were bombing in Afghanistan. I said, "Are we still going to war with Iraq?" And he said, "Oh, it's worse than that." He reached over on his desk. He picked up a piece of paper. And he said, "I just got this down from upstairs" -- meaning the Secretary of Defense's office -- "today." And he said, "This is a memo that describes how we're going to take out seven countries in five years, starting with Iraq, and then Syria, Lebanon, Libya, Somalia, Sudan and, finishing off, Iran." I said, "Is it classified?" He said, "Yes, sir." I said, "Well, don't show it to me." And I saw him a year or so ago, and I said, "You remember that?" He said, "Sir, I didn't show you that memo! I didn't show it to you!" iran taken over by radical muslims with cia help=now bribe dems to support iran deal

snippet.textDisplay: A few things, if he's the only one lending to the poor, whether they can pay it back or not, then he is the reason they are able to buy things. And there is no gender pay inequality; it's been debunked countless times. The average man makes more money than the average woman because the genders trend towards different choices. Men are more likely to work long hours in miserable conditions, to work in dangerous jobs, to work with machines, or medicine, or something technical. Women are more likely to work with people, as teachers, or whatever. Not everyone will follow these trends of course, but the trends still exist. When a man and a woman work the same job, at the same company, and the same hours, the difference almost disappears, and may come down to things like negotiation. In fact, sometimes a random woman will earn more than a random man in the same job. So it's clearly nonsense. And you know what else? In, I believe it's Switzerland, women earn more than men on average (still not because of the reasons you think), and this was seen as a victory for gender equality. People who spout this narrative don't want equality: they push for equality of outcome rather than equality under the law, which will always require a tremendous amount of meddling into people's lives, but they don't want equality. They want women to have it better than men, and in many ways, they already do. Fuck socialism. Fuck feminism. Fuck the government. Let people do what they want as long as they don't hurt anyone. The end.
snippet.textOriginal: A few things, if he's the only one lending to the poor, whether they can pay it back or not, then he is the reason they are able to buy things.  And there is no gender pay inequality; it's been debunked countless times.  The average man makes more money than the average woman because the genders trend towards different choices.  Men are more likely to work long hours in miserable conditions, to work in dangerous jobs, to work with machines, or medicine, or something technical.  Women are more likely to work with people, as teachers, or whatever.  Not everyone will follow these trends of course, but the trends still exist.  When a man and a woman work the same job, at the same company, and the same hours, the difference almost disappears, and may come down to things like negotiation.  In fact, sometimes a random woman will earn more than a random man in the same job.  So it's clearly nonsense.  And you know what else?  In, I believe it's Switzerland, women earn more than men on average (still not because of the reasons you think), and this was seen as a victory for gender equality.  People who spout this narrative don't want equality: they push for equality of outcome rather than equality under the law, which will always require a tremendous amount of meddling into people's lives, but they don't _want_ equality.  They want women to have it better than men, and in many ways, they already do.  Fuck socialism.  Fuck feminism.  Fuck the government.  Let people do what they want as long as they don't hurt anyone.  The end.
